              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "PPAC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Low-mass multiple gas-filled parallel-plate",
                "avalanche counter was used for fission fragment",
                "detection. Fissionable material was electrodeposited",
                "over 10 titanium foils of 3 mu-m thickness. Each",
                "titanium foil is sandwiched between two 2.5 mu-m",
                "aluminum foils, forming the cathode. Two anodes, made",
                "of the same thickness aluminum foil, are placed at",
                "either side of cathode with a separation distance of",
                "3 mm. Incident neutron energy was determined by time",
                "of flight."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SCIN"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Neutrons and gamma rays emitted by the",
                "fragments were measured using the Chi-Nu liquid",
                "scintillator array, a hemispherical array of 54 EJ-",
                "309 organic scintillator detectors. Detectors were",
                "placed at a distance of 1 m from the fission chamber."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
